article.headline: CS Northridge 73, Cal Lutheran 62
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- Josh Jenkins scored 16 points and Tony Osunsanmi grabbed 14 rebounds off the bench to lead California State, Northridge to a 73-62 victory over Cal Lutheran on Friday night. Jenkins hit 7-of-12 shots and added five steals and four assists. Osunsanmi added seven points, two steals. His previous rebounding best was six last year against Rider College. Aaron Fisher and Kyle Knudsen scored 16 points apiece for Cal Lutheran. Fisher also led Cal Lutheran rebounders with 10. Cal Lutheran was outrebounded 47-39 and was only 19-of-34 from the free throw line.
